iguring out how to manage visibility is crucial.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Addressing class loading concerns**\\n\\nI’m considering how a URLClassLoader that points at code sources or test classes could define a class that the app hasn’t already loaded. However, if a nested class is referenced in the test class signature, it would get loaded by the app. I want a distinct interface not loaded by the app using a class literal. Using a nested class name string might work, but the test shouldn't rely on reflection unless it's necessary for public APIs. I'll explore alternatives like using a ServiceLoader or defining inner interfaces with a custom ClassLoader.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring class and proxy issues**\\n\\nI’m considering using `java.sql.Driver` from the platform class loader as both the extraType and type in the app. The candidate (platform) cannot load the type, which could lead to false hits on line 104. However, Proxy.newProxyInstance will use typeClassLoader if it fails and includes interfaces for both type and extraType. Since the app class loader can see java.sql.Driver and the test type, the proxy should work. I also need to look at line 43 and make sure that interfaces are public or at least accessible.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_XCVkvt5LeRMQX3ZQMQfdApMp|fc_0a7137ada349f8ba016a4262d3903881978f70167472881c99", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.quarkus/quarkus-bootstrap-gradle-resolver/3.33.1/src/test/java/io_quarkus/quarkus_bootstrap_gradle_resolver/OrgGradleInternalClassloaderClasspathUtilTest.java", "limit": 220}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2312, "output": 1007, "cacheRead": 18432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21751, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782735554543, "responseId": "resp_0a7137ada349f8ba016a4262c30cc48197a3679b9120